---
// src/components/FootnotesHeading.astro
//
// The "Footnotes" label that introduces the footnote items at the
// bottom of an essay. Rendered as a styled <p>, NOT an <h2>, so it
// never lands in the rehype-slug heading tree — meaning the auto-
// generated table of contents stays clean for essays that have body
// H2s. (The "Footnotes" entry would otherwise pollute every ToC.)
//
// Pairs with <EssayBreak />, which renders the asterism above the
// footnote apparatus. Standard authoring shape in MDX:
//
//   <EssayBreak />
//
//   <FootnotesHeading />
//
//   <Footnote id="1">First footnote text.</Footnote>
//
// Or with editorial content between them (acknowledgments, etc.):
//
//   <EssayBreak />
//
//   *Some prose, e.g. photo credits.*
//
//   <FootnotesHeading />
//
//   <Footnote id="1">...</Footnote>
//
// If you ever want a different label ("Notes", "References"), add an
// optional `label` prop here. v1 is fixed at "Footnotes" because that's
// what these are.
//
// Replaced the previous <FootnoteSection /> component (April 2026)
// alongside <EssayBreak />.
//
// Styles for .essay-footnote-heading live in EssayLayout.astro's
// <style is:global> block; this component contributes only the markup.
---

<p class="essay-footnote-heading">Footnotes</p>
